{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida89b0bdc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1129a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1129a"},"text":"§ 1129a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Purple Heart: members killed or wounded in attacks by foreign terrorist organizations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida89b0bdd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1129a/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In General","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of the award of the Purple Heart, the Secretary concerned shall treat a member of the armed forces described in subsection (b) in the same manner as a member who is killed or wounded as a result of an international terrorist attack against the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida89b0bde-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1129a/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Covered Members","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida89b0bdf-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1129a/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A member described in this subsection is a member on active duty who was killed or wounded in an attack by a foreign terrorist organization in circumstances where the death or wound is the result of an attack targeted on the member due to such member’s status as a member of the armed forces, unless the death or wound is the result of willful misconduct of the member.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida89b0be0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1129a/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" For purposes of this section, an attack by an individual or entity shall be considered to be an attack by a foreign terrorist organization if—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida89b0be1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1129a/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the individual or entity was in communication with the foreign terrorist organization before the attack; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida89b0be2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1129a/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the attack was inspired or motivated by the foreign terrorist organization.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida89b0be3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1129a/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Foreign Terrorist Organization Defined","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In this section, the term “foreign terrorist organization” means an entity designated as a foreign terrorist organization by the Secretary of State pursuant to section 219 of the Immigration and Nationality Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t8/s1189"},"text":"8 U.S.C. 1189","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida89b0be4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/291/dA/tV/s571/a/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–291, div. A, title V, § 571(a)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3387"},"text":"128 Stat. 3387","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida89b0be5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"ida89b0be6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"ida89b0be7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Retroactive Effective Date and Application","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/291/dA/tV/s571/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–291, div. A, title V, § 571(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3387"},"text":"128 Stat. 3387","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/113/291/dA/tV/s571/a/2"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"“(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Effective date","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The amendments made by paragraph (1) [enacting this section] shall take effect as of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-09-11"},"text":"September 11, 2001","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Review of certain previous incidents","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary concerned shall undertake a review of each death or wounding of a member of the Armed Forces that occurred between ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-09-11"},"text":"September 11, 2001","children":[],"tail":", and the date of the enactment of this Act ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":"] under circumstances that could qualify as being the result of an attack described in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1129a"},"text":"section 1129a of title 10","children":[],"tail":", United States Code (as added by paragraph (1)), to determine whether the death or wounding qualifies as a death or wounding resulting from an attack by a foreign terrorist organization for purposes of the award of the Purple Heart pursuant to such section (as so added)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"“(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Actions following review","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"If the death or wounding of a member of the Armed Forces reviewed under subparagraph (B) is determined to qualify as a death or wounding resulting from an attack by a foreign terrorist organization as described in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1129a"},"text":"section 1129a of title 10","children":[],"tail":", United States Code (as so added), the Secretary concerned shall take appropriate action under such section to award the Purple Heart to the member."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"“(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Secretary concerned defined","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In this paragraph, the term ‘Secretary concerned’ has the meaning given that term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s101/a/9"},"text":"section 101(a)(9) of title 10","children":[],"tail":", United States Code.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
